<title>LUXEMBOURG: EU to study drought aid for Portugal cereals farms.</title>
<headline>EU to study drought aid for Portugal cereals farms.</headline>
<dateline>LUXEMBOURG 1997-04-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>The European Union will study possible aid for Portuguese cereals and oilseeds farmers after drought destroyed a large part of the crop, EU Farm Commissioner Franz Fischler said on Tuesday.</p>
<p>Portuguese Farm Minister Fernando Gomes da Silva told a meeting of EU farm ministers that March was the driest in Portugal for 100 years and he would send a detailed report on the extent of the crop damage and proposals for action.</p>
<p>&quot;We have a very difficult situation for cereals and oilseeds,&quot; Gomes da Silva earlier told Reuters, adding, &quot;Drought is not just a Portuguese problem -- look at France, Spain, Italy, Luxembourg, Britain.&quot;</p>
</text>
